725780f-a.text:
One Hundred Ninth Ave. (Suwanee Ave.), at the N.W. corner of Pinegrove Street (formerly Allen Street.), showing the Greenwood house. In 1909 this property contained 8O acres and belonged to A. Van Sicklen. Note: that if locating under old location, it would be Lincoln Ave., south side, opposite Allen Street. The house was still standing in
1931.
About 1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
